title: For Sale:  PVS-15 Gen 3 Night Vision Goggles - Like New! Full Kit!
postcontent:
I am the original owner and purchased these BRAND NEW in August 2014 from Wilcox Engineering (Ed Wilcox is a living legend in the night vision world). These are the full kit MARSOC NVBS-15 Gen 3 Night Vision Goggles still in use by both Marine and Army SOF. I have the original Wilcox invoice (pictured below), showing these have over a YEAR remaining on the Wilcox warranty (Aug 2016)!

As you can see by the invoice, these have Omni VII MX-10160A tubes installed. These tubes are NOT autogated, something I specifically wanted since I live in rural farm country. This means these 15's are COMPLETELY SILENT (the night vision "whine" you hear in movies comes from "Autogating" power supplies, which can be NOISY!) If you're an urban door-kicking high-speed death machine, you may want to have autogated tubes. The left tube has two factory blemishes (normal) -- one on the extreme outer edge of Zone-3 at the 1:00 position, and a small one at the outer edge of Zone-2 at about 2:00. NO BLEMS IN ZONE 1. The right tube has a few flecks, but nothing major.

I can take PayPal, but prefer cash (obviously) for FTF transactions. My ID matches the Wilcox invoice (both name and address), these were NOT originally sold to the military (i.e. they are NOT stolen US.GOV property!!!). Happy to meet up at night here in Cowtown, USA for you to try them out and see what a gorgeous set of SOF-spec Gen 3 NV goggles are all about. If you haven't experience dual tubes, or real Gen 3 NV, prepare to have your mind blown! These NVBS-15 are WATERPROOF and are spec'd to be submersible to 66-feet UNDER WATER! They're lighter than the older-style PVS-15, and the tubes articulate independently -- a HUGE benefit when you want to shoulder a rifle while keeping your night vision view over the other eye!

Call, text, email for more info or to make offers. I still have the original battery in them, and have used them for fewer than 20 hours (on tubes that will last >10,000 hours of power-on time!).

title: For Sale:  G-Code Incog Glock 19/26 23/27
postcontent:
INCOG is a joint development project between Haley Strategic Partners and G-Code Holsters. 

The INCOG is a minimum bulk, multi-positional, deep concealment holster. Its distinctive features enable the concealed carry of a handgun from a variety of carry positions while facilitating the acquisition of a full firing grip on the weapon prior to the draw. Inherent are adjustments in the depth of carry, angle of carry, the position of carry and security of carry. Adjustments are supported via the unique modular mounting points on the holster and the use of variable mounting components. Combined they maximize function respective to the users: body type, deployment tactics and personal preferences. The holster is adaptive to varying operational environments and mission requirements. 

The mounting clip Incorporates a negative angle designed to force the holster closer to the body. This improves the conceal-ability of the holster without increasing the bulk and supports a higher positional carry without compromise to the positional security of the holster during use. This higher position facilitates faster weapon presentations from deep cover. The mounting clips also have multiple mounting points further increasing the range of carry options and adjustments. The mounting clips open and slide down over the belt and lock in place. The clip is actuated via a finger tab, and is flexed to open allowing quick installation or removal from the belt. 


All INCOG holsters come with either a Tactical Fuzz or Camo Coating are available with black, gray or green Kydex.
